<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Having the following form element (in this case using annotations):</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
/**
 * @Annotation\Type("Zend\Form\Element\MultiCheckbox")
 * @Annotation\Attributes({"options": {1: "opt1", 2: "opt2"}})
 * @Annotation\Options({"label": "LabelText"})
 */
protected $elem;</code></pre>

<p>And using the FormRow view helper in a view renders a single checkbox instead of a fieldset containing all checkboxes.
This is because the view helper checks the element's type:</p>

<p>```</p>

<p>However, a MultiCheckbox element has the attribute type "checkbox".</p>

<p>Trying to workaround this and setting the attribute's tpye to "multicheckbox" renders the desired fieldset, but breaks the element itself (renders a textfield as "multicheckbox" will be the HTML node's type attribute).</p>

